# Dependency Boundaries

- **No cyclic dependencies:** Modules/packages/services must not depend on each other in cycles.
- **Local-first dependencies:** Declare a dependency in the closest module/package that actually uses it.
- **Root/shared dependency criteria:** Only promote dependencies to a shared/root layer when two or more modules genuinely require them.
- **Boundary ownership:** Keep domain-level modules independent from application/adapter layers that depend on them.
- **Direction clarity:** Define and preserve one-way dependency flow between layers.

## Review Expectations

- If a new dependency is introduced, explain why it belongs at that layer.
- If a dependency is shared centrally, document which modules require it.
- If a boundary exception is unavoidable, add a short rationale and follow-up refactor note.
